text: The Women's Doubles tournament at the 1969 French Open was held from 26 May to 8 June 1969 on the outdoor clay courts at the Stade Roland Garros in Paris, France. The third-seeded team of Françoise Dürr and Ann Jones won the title, defeating the first-seeded pair of Margaret Court and Nancy Richey in the final in three sets. ==Seeds== ==Draw== ===Finals=== === Top half === ==== Section 1 ==== ==== Section 2 ==== === Bottom half === ==== Section 3 ==== ==== Section 4 ==== == References == ==External links== * Main draw *1969 French Open – Women's draws and results at the International Tennis Federation Women's Doubles Category:French Open by year – Women's Doubles Category:1969 in women's tennis
